    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "You have a couple of testnets available for running here: https://github.com/eth2-clients/eth2-testnets feel free to pick one.\r\n\r\nRegarding the RANDAO it is specified here: https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/blob/dev/specs/core/0_beacon-chain.md#randao\r\n\r\n```python\r\ndef process_randao(state: BeaconState, body: BeaconBlockBody) -> None:\r\n    epoch = get_current_epoch(state)\r\n    # Verify RANDAO reveal\r\n    proposer = state.validators[get_beacon_proposer_index(state)]\r\n    assert bls_verify(proposer.pubkey, hash_tree_root(epoch), body.randao_reveal, get_domain(state, DOMAIN_RANDAO))\r\n    # Mix in RANDAO reveal\r\n    mix = xor(get_randao_mix(state, epoch), hash(body.randao_reveal))\r\n    state.randao_mixes[epoch % EPOCHS_PER_HISTORICAL_VECTOR] = mix\r\n```\r\n\r\nwith randao mix being just an array storing crypto mixes\r\n```python\r\ndef get_randao_mix(state: BeaconState, epoch: Epoch) -> Bytes32:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Return the randao mix at a recent ``epoch``.\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    return state.randao_mixes[epoch % EPOCHS_PER_HISTORICAL_VECTOR]\r\n```\r\n\r\nHash being sha256, and randao_reveal being derived from user private data and the source of entropy.\r\n\r\nThe spec is executable so you can run it and dissect how every elements work, please see instructions here: https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/tree/dev/test_libs/pyspec\r\n\r\nPS: As a general advice, I understand that you might be either excited or pressed for time or not be a native English speaker but your title and your text could be seen as rude and/or spammy due to the special characters to draw attention and the massive amount of exclamation marks.\r\n",
